name: Zevo Ant, Roach and Spider Crawling Insect Spray, 10 oz
comments: It says “spray insects” which indicates it's not for pest control but to kill the bugs you currently see.  This product is not spray and it dries.  Nope, it is for spray, wait for the bugs to die and then dry the area with paper towels.  This product leaves a extremely oily residue that does not dry and is NOT easy to clean up.  I will include a pictures of what a “quick spray” of this product left behind when I used it around my kitchen trash can.  It took 15 paper towels and then I had to use a spray bottle of vinegar and water to mop the rest up.  The odor of this product IS NOT for those who have a sensitive nose.  It is so overpowering and I cannot and will not use it again.  With the oily residue, I was sure glad the ants were on my tile and not running along a baseboard in a carpeted room or along one of my rugs.  I took the pictures an hour after I sprayed this product…it was not dry.  I just cannot handle the residue or the odor.  I will be looking for another pet and people safe product to use.

Found it even work better smashing them roaches with my hands then this spray.  Don't even think about getting this stuff in your eyes be burning for days.  Not so safe after y'all saying natural.    Stick to the professional bug killas my complex paid for once I was complaining.  No more roaches after they spray.  They did come back three times but now I don't see nothing and my family live in peace.

I had to spray the ants 2 times and wait a couple of more seconds before I saw them dying. The smell of this product is also very strong and not my favorite. I will be sticking to my normal brand.

Bought a bottle this years and the ants were killed... For a day. Used the entire gallon just on the back of my house over the course of a week. The ants were back the very next day every time. I went to my basement and found what was left of last years bottle(i used it last year inside and out in my house and had left over),  and since i didn't have much left I sprayed just the problem areas. (The back of my house where i wasted an entire gallon of this years product.)  The ants are gone. Its been 4 days and they haven't come back. So as my titla says it used to be great but apparently they decided to upgrade to a wand so that its easier to apply, but changed to an inferior product that no longer works. I would much rather pumo spray a product that is effective than wand a prduct that might as well be water.

Hot Shot 7832991 17.5 oz Ant, Roach & Spider Killer
comments:
Hot Shot DOES NOT kill roaches.  

I was five inches away from a countertop full of them (yes- disgusting) and was DRENCHING them in this stuff.  Some of them were doing an impressive backstroke in the growing puddle of “Hot Shot,” but they weren't expiring.  

Mind you- all of them were “under water”- completely immersed in the liquid from the can.

Unless there is a delayed reaction where they go home and die in their sleep after they go to sleep it off, all this stuff does is make them flail around.  A couple of them were staggering a little as they went back to their hidey holes after they got out of the pool, but none of them died right in front of me.  Not one.

Maybe it kills little baby ones [edit: no, it doesn't] but the ones in here are about three quarters of an inch long.  They are just your standard roaches- we don't live next door to Three Mile Island or anything.  And while they appeared briefly disoriented after being sprayed, not one of them expired that I could see.

So “Kills On Contact” is not true.  “Fast Knockdown” is not true either, unless this term refers to them falling over before learning the backstroke really fast before scampering off.  This product should be called “Shower Time for Roaches,” not Hot Shot.  It doesn't stink and has a rather pleasant scent, but I didn't buy it because I needed an air freshener.  Maybe the roaches like the smell- I don't know.

I'm stuck with two full cans of this crap with bugs everywhere.  …Well- it is making ME feel funny.  Maybe it makes you so woozy you forget the bugs are there.  Oh- and it will give you a headache. 

Spend the dollar plus whatever more, and get Raid.  That stuff does the job.  This stuff is garbage. 

(I tried an experiment.  I sprayed a baby roach in order to observe the “effects” of this product under more controlled circumstances.  I squirted it.  It ran away from the wetness, then stopped.  Ah, thought I- it's dead.  Nope.  I had just given it a “time out,” and after a few moments of walking a little irregularly, it “stood up straight” and walked away as if nothing had happened to it.  I thought I may have heard a tiny “Thanks for the free bath, lady!” as it vanished.)

comments: Bought one and the string broke after the spider was hung up and activated 3 times. Figured it was a fluke, so bought a second one. Hung the new one up but kept it off for a few days just to be sure this one was sturdier than my previous one. Turned it on after 5 days of hanging just fine and the string snapped almost immediately as the spider started to descend. There is no way to reattach the hoop to the string that's inside the spider so they are both paperweights now. The string is LITERALLY about as thick as a strand of hair. So, save your money and buy a different brand if you're looking for something like this. The only positive I can say, is that the sound it made was clear, easy to hear, and kinda cool.

name: Heroes Of Goo Jit Zu Marvel Hero, The Amazing Spider-Man - Squishy, 4.5" Tall, Boys, Ages 4+
comments: I overall did not care for the Marvel Heros Goo Jit Zu Spider Man. The first thing I noticed is that the eyes were completely different sizes.  I expected the figure to be super stretchy which he was,  however seeing the water beads was not really achievable at all.  I would not get this again.

I really don't like to give a review that's not 100% honest 
because I sometimes base the products I purchase by 
reading feedback first! I wanted so bad to like this product 
because I love smelling mint. This spray is just too much 
of a mint smell to use inside. It's very overwhelming so
I thought maybe that's what would get rid of the spiders
and bugs. It just didn't seem to be killing the bugs so I 
thought maybe it just repells them. The smell maybe keeps 
them away.
The Mighty mint smells so strong that my dog hides
when she see me bring the bottle out! I am not a fan of 
this product and I think I would purchase it!
